#: admin/tab-templates/bupr-setting-support-tab.php:24
msgid "How can we submit a review to a member profile using this plugin?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/tab-templates/bupr-setting-support-tab.php:28
msgid "When visiting the \"/members\" section on the site, go to the single profile view page. There you can see a menu named \"Reviews\" which will allow you to add a profile review only if you are a member."
msgstr ""

#: admin/tab-templates/bupr-setting-support-tab.php:36
msgid "How can we add more rating criteria for the review form?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/tab-templates/bupr-setting-support-tab.php:40
msgid "Just go to \"Dashboard->Review->BP member review settings page\" and click the \"Add Criteria\" button to add more fields. Then click the \"Save Settings\" button to update the review settings."
msgstr ""

#: admin/tab-templates/bupr-setting-support-tab.php:48
msgid "What is the Top Members widget and how do I use it?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/tab-templates/bupr-setting-support-tab.php:52
msgid "The Members Review widget displays a list of members on the site front-end. When you successfully activate the BP Member Profile Review plugin, you can see the Members Review widget in the widget section."
msgstr ""

#: admin/tab-templates/bupr-setting-support-tab.php:60
msgid "Can I use the review form on any other page?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/tab-templates/bupr-setting-support-tab.php:63
msgid "Yes, you can use the review form on another page. Just copy the shortcode from the review settings page and paste it on the other page."
msgstr ""

#: admin/tab-templates/bupr-setting-support-tab.php:70
msgid "What should I do if I am unable to publish the shortcode page after updating to WordPress 5.0?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/tab-templates/bupr-setting-support-tab.php:73
msgid "Install the Classic Editor plugin. Then, in the right sidebar, you’ll see a link for “use classic editor”."
msgstr ""

